anklefootright.label: Range of Motion: AMA Guides Expected Normal Ranges (page 598 Table A-3) Extension: 20, Flexion: 40, Inversion: 30, Eversion: 20. Motion is measured with goniometer and is reported right over left side in Degrees (D).

Actual goniometer measurements of the range of motion are only required for PR-4 (Permanent & Stationary) reports. Visual estimates of the range of motion may be adequate for Doctor's First reports and PR-2 reports.
